<paragraph blockId="10.[443,822,1408,1432]" box="[443,822,1408,1432]" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">
<heading box="[443,822,1408,1432]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238" reason="3">
<taxonomicName authority="(Philippi, 1846)" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[443,822,1408,1432]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Lithophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytilida" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="teres">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[443,634,1408,1432]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">Lithophaga teres</emphasis>
(Philippi, 1846)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[154,1110,1472,1563]" box="[194,856,1472,1497]" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">
<emphasis box="[194,288,1473,1497]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">Habitat.</emphasis>
Boring into dead coral and the limestone rock.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="3238" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[154,1110,1472,1563]" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">
<emphasis box="[194,335,1508,1532]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">Distribution.</emphasis>
Despite the abundance of coral debris and the limestone rocks the frequency of this, and other date mussels, appears to be low.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[154,1110,1575,1665]" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">
<emphasis box="[194,301,1575,1599]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">Remarks.</emphasis>
This black-shelled species often co-occurs with the pale-coloured 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamy" authorityYear="1919" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Lithophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytilida" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">L. robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two are also distinguished on shell shape with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamy" authorityYear="1919" box="[898,1020,1607,1631]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Lithophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytilida" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[898,1020,1607,1631]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">L. robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having more prominent umbos and curved ligament margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[194,812,1676,1733]" box="[194,532,1676,1700]" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">
<emphasis box="[194,272,1676,1700]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">Range.</emphasis>
Indo-Pacific [R/M/S].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[194,812,1676,1733]" box="[194,812,1708,1733]" pageId="10" pageNumber="3238">
